SIMPLE: foretaste
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foretaste
<hw>Fore"taste`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A taste
beforehand; enjoyment in advance; anticipation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foretaste</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Foretaste
<hw>Fore*taste"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
taste before full possession; to have previous enjoyment or experience
of; to anticipate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To taste before another.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Foretasted</xex> fruit.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foretaster</ent>⟦br⟧
